entry.key: This is the guy who’s smile turns your knees to jello and I just wanted to say one thing.
entry.value: 我是那个微笑可以让你的膝盖变成凝胶物的人。

entry.key: I knew that a phrase such as "frequent flyer," "hatch-back," or "Jello shot" would in time make a poem sound dated and thus could drastically shorten its shelf life.
entry.value: 我知道，像"frequent flyer"(航空哩程累计法)，"hatch-back"(后仓式) " 或"Jello shot"(果子冻饮料)这样的词汇迟早会使一首诗失去新意，可能大大缩短作品的所谓"货架寿命"(Shelf Life)。"

entry.key: This jello model of Scottsdale, Arizona is on display at a local performing arts center.
entry.value: 这种凝胶物模型正在亚利桑那州斯科特斯德市当地的展览艺术中心展出。
